caption: I genuinely love this place.  It's quaint with excellent service.  The only reason I gave it 4 stars is because the pizza wasn't anything wonderful or to call home about.  It was good, and clearly fresh.  I would definitely go back, however.

I support the good restaurants, support whoever works right. pizza here has a taste of heaven. Best choice, Bambino Spinach Supreme! Toasted Ravioli. Wow .. I must have missed a lot of other good things. We thank you again for making our Valentine's Day with the family and the food so amazing. We definitely recommend it .. the food is the eye before the stomach.

Pequod's has the best deep dish Bacino's has the best stuffed pizza To compare the two is apples to oranges  I don't like that Bacino's claims "1st heart healthy pizza" though.  There's no such thing as a heart healthy pizza.  Their seating needs to be updated.  The booths will hurt your back.  They could use a restroom update also.  But, these are minor complaints.  The food is amazing, including their appetizers.  I live on the southside of Chicago but never mind taking a 45 min trip up to Bacino's.

I came here for Valentine's Day to get their heart shaped deep dish. It was delicious and I actually preferred this place to Giordano's! The atmosphere was very nostalgic for me as it reminded me of the East coast pizza places I used to visit as a kid. Definitely coming back here (also the picture has a snapchat filter on it but it's the only one I took of it, sorry!!)

Bacino's has all the classic toppings you could want and is made with quality, fresh ingredients. It is affordable and tastes handmade! I have been eating Bacino's pizza since I was a child and I am happy they have stayed in the neighborhood this long.
Horrible manager
The food is awesome,  makes me happy.
Best toasted ravioli. Stuffed pizza was amazing. If I could rate this place higher than 5 stars I would.
Do yourself a favor and order the spinach supreme thin crust pizza with mushrooms. Amazing pizza, kind staff, speedy service/take out/delivery.

First time in Chicago and this was not only the best pizza we had here, but the best food we have found in Chicago overall. There tiramisu was ridiculously good and the staff was very very friendly too!  If I’m ever back in Chicago I’m coming here again without a doubt
Hands down the best customer service I ever received!! Pizza was amazing, super friendly staff. Thank you !!  Ashley Sierra from AZ

Love this place! We always went to Giordano's growing up- which I am also a fan of. I don't love the corn crusts at Lou Malnati's (Uno's is better than LM). More of a Gino's/ Giordano's type deep dish fan. I like Pequod's too, but wish their cheese to crust ratio was better. Ricobene's is good too, but I only ever want to get a King steak from them because it's the best sandwich in the world.  Bacino's is my new favorite deep dish. I hadn't had their pizza until my brother ordered it when visiting last year- and he tried it once- like 20 years ago at the Taste. His 5 year old son loved it too!! I wish I knew about them sooner & will def keep ordering from them.  I usually always get a deep dish pie- it's amazing. The thin crust I tried once and was also very good-similar to Giordano's thin crust. I would not recommend the extra thin for delivery. I also am not an ultra thin fan, unless I'm making it at home and eating it immediately.  It's really the sauce- I love the saltiness, acidity and the fact that it is not sweet. I've also never gotten a soggy crust on a deep dish pie from here- which is one of the biggest disappointments in getting a stuffed pizza.
Terrible pizza - the crust tastes like cardboard, way too much sauce - that has to be out of a can, and overall just gross.
Very welcoming and delicious......
Amazing pizza and its atmosphere is cozy and quiet

Bacinos stuffed pizza’s have been my families favorite for over 30 years! It is made with the freshest ingredients and absolutely delicious! I’m born and raised Chicagoan so I know great tasting pizza. Thank goodness they ship to my home in SW Florida so we don’t ever have to go without the best stuffed pizza everrr!
GREAT Chicago deep dish pizza...but they have thin crust too!!
Delicious Bird on da Grill Panini, Italian Beef, and tiramisu! Excited to try some of their pizzas and salads next!

It was incredible. The service was very good, they made sure we were taken care of and checked in during good times. We got the Stuffed Portabyella. It was absolutely delicious and so unique. When we got our pizza we were in awe of how amazingly cheesy and just awesome it looked. It tasted so good. The sauce was light and tasted so fresh. The cheese was so good. It was a perfect mix of stretchy and chewy and had an amazing rich taste. The prizes were really good. I highly recommend this place :)
Anything under a 5 star wOuld be a disgrace. This is a Covid review, and they knocked it out of the park. I will be coming here 2-3 times a week. It’s amazing!!
Just discovered this place last month. Probably ordered it 5x within that time period. The thin crust is really good.
Pretty good deep dish. Standard crust (vs cornmeal). Nothing out of the ordinary.

You haven't had pizza until you've had Chicago deep dish here! I bought 3 for my husband and son and we didn't even finish the first one it was so filling! Will definitely come back if I'm back in town!
Ordered delivery. Couldn't contact them. Even GrubHub couldn't get ahold of them. Had to cancel the order after it was 30 minutes late. I don't mind waiting but damn. They dropped the ball.
Best pizza try the rost beef
Had a wondey time!!!!

This is our neighborhood pizza spot and I couldn't be more thrilled that we moved in so close to it! The food is delicious (thin crust giardinieria with half sausage is our go-to!), the staff is so sweet, and the owner places personal follow-up calls to ensure we had a good experience. That's unheard of customer service. I'm proud to put my dollars toward this local business and would highly recommend you do the same if you're in the area!
Best Pizza in Chicago. The crust is perfection also.
Delicious Bird on da Grill Panini, Italian Beef, and tiramisu! Excited to try some of their pizzas and salads next!
Awesome thin crust!!!

I have been a regular customer for about 30 years. They have always been consistent with a delicious pizza. My visiting out of town relatives always request at least one visit to Bacinos during their visit.
Very fun! I loved the pizza. I wish I could handle eating more. It is filling. Clean. Nice staff. The Wizard of Oz park is right down the street. We took an Uber to get there and back to the hotel.
Some of the best Chicago deep dish in the area. After eating there, I get one to take back to Iowa. Good beer selection too.
Small, low key, but great food, staff, and service.
Great food, great service great prices
They offer a fantastic range of fresh food. I enjoy eating here. Employees are always helpful, rates are reasonable and the place is always neat.
I love the pizza
There is not much to say they have great pizza and great service we will definitely come back !

Seriously one of the worst stuffed, really any kind, pizza I've ever tried. From pickup to the 5 minute drive home. The pizza had run water/grease out of a corner onto my seat, fused to the cardboard bottom and we had to tear off each piece minus the bottom of the crust or literally eat cardboard. Meatballs were just ok. Garlic bread was good, though. 👍
We ordered thin crust pizza, I've had much better. We also had calamari and a salad which were good, especially the salad dressing

Better than ever!  I got hooked on the stuffed spinach and mushroom pizzas at this store in 1982.  I couldn’t imagine they could be any better, but last night they were (on a carry out that we had to keep warm in the oven for an hour, no less).  Keep up the great work, Miguel and company.  Really nice folks over here, as well, by the way.
one of the best pizza places and there prices are great for a deep dish you will be pleasantly surprised!
Best pizza  period
I think I came here to get meatball sandwiches.
Thin crust Margherita pizza with garlic butter substitution. Delicious!  Wish we could get this delivered to ALASKA!!!
Deep dish pizza was delicious. Server was very helpful and nice also. Would definitely recommend this place.
had a bad experience back in March, and a TERRIBLE one here on 9/2. See my yelp review for more details. They lost a customer.

If you want pizza the way it’s supposed to be prepared, Bacino’s is that place. The crust was thin and plenty of cheese and spinach. Simply delicious!! The pizza is among the best I’ve had. Great, friendly service.

Great pit stop walikng back to ild town feom Wrigley!

Just finished eating here with my fiancé. Towards the end of the meal, I found a large roach crawling around my water cup. Immediately disgusted, I called a waitress over and I killed it with my cup. The customer service was horrible as well as our two apps and small stuffed pizza came at the same time. We were still forced to pay half of our check by the manager who had also happened to be our waitress. I will be calling later to complain in someone else’s ear. Oh, also, when we first sat down, there were two dirty butter knives that were under our table that looked like they were there for a few days. Dirty place. Highly disappointing.

It was lunch time. Super chill. Price: buffalo wings, fries, caprese salad, deep dish L spinach supreme - $60 Service: such pleasant personnel, very attentive and very nice. Food: we are New Englanders and deep dish will never replace our traditional thin pizza, but this was great. Very cheesey, lots of spinach and mushrooms. The pizza sauce was so fresh and tangy, loved it. Overall: yes

I worked at the wacker location almost 40 years ago. That's when I discovered how amazing a stuffed spinach and mushroom pizza can be. When I was at church I would go to the Lincoln park location. I ate Bacino's a few times a week until I moved out of Chicago. Chicago stuffed pizza is the best and Bacino's is the best of the best. I have lived all over the country and Asia for several years and I used to order the half baked frozen, but then you stopped. I have to make them myself and it takes a lot of work so I only get to have it once or twice a year now :-( I used to recommend your pizza to everyone when I was in college and worked hospitality in Chicago and now that I live out of state, I still recommend you to anyone traveling there. Please consider offering shipping again.
Delicious pizza!!!!
It took a little longer than I would have liked, but once we received our food it was definitely worth the wait! Not to mention it was very affordable!

Very delicious! Great staff. Quality Chicago pizza. I recommend Bacino's to all travelers and of course locals. We had a table of 8. 2 pizzas was enough.

Amazing and traditional place in Chicago! I was in the city for only three days and I was looking for a place exactly like this one to try for the first time the famous Chicago’s Stuffed Pizza! Very good experience with a great and cold Stella Artois. Looking forward to go back in the city and try other flavors!!

Bacino's is okay but the service is pretty bad. Honestly, in Chicago, the food industry competition's stiff - a restaurant can have decent food but the waitstaff can make or break its reputation. I ate here not long ago. It wasn't crowded - two tables - but my waitress was so busy flirting with the four men at the other table that she seemed really annoyed at having to wait on me, too. I'm pretty low maintenance - I like to eat and write without being bothered - so her eye rolls and loud sighs at having to bring me silverware barely registered. But I had my food all of five minutes when she came over and asked "you want me to get you a to go box or something?" So. Weird. Anyway, the food was okay (I had the bolognese).  Would I eat here again if I happen to be walking by? Maybe. Would I go out of my way to come here? No.  Things to know: street parking, have to go downstairs to use the bathroom

I love this spot. They serve my favorite Chicago style deep dish pizza! I go for the classic; sausage, peppers, onions, mushrooms or the spinach supreme with or without mushrooms, the cheese blend is off the hook! Great beer at a reasonable (neighborhood surcharge) cost and kisses at the end of the meal, if you're lucky! Try the place it's a real contender on the deep dish scene.
The best EVER! The sauce is amazing! We shared a small pepperoni and it was more than enough for 2 people. We come to Chicago atleast once a year and everytime we have to come here for the pizza.
Top notch deep dish pizza.  I had plenty of left overs for days. Friendly staff and great beer prices.
I ate a delicious pizza, you should try it!

We love coming here after our visit at Lincoln Park zoo.  It is only a 10 minute (or so) walk from the zoo.  The food is always good when we come.  We typically just order a pizza and an appetizer.  The staff has always been friendly.
Very nice pizza, maybe slightly spicy but taste is really good. Each portion is giant and fill of cheese, recommended to go visit on group to taste different pizzas

The food is a 5 but the bathrooms downstairs were dirty, in disrepair and had bugs. The place is run down with holes and broken springs in the booth seats. Next time Ill get take out...

As first time visitors to Chicago, this place exceeded our expectations of deep dish pizza! Great service, value and the pizza is out of this world. Thank you Bacino's, we will definitely be back.
Best pizza (deep dish) I have ever had. Been to 2 other well know Chicago pizza restaurants and this was the best one!

We fell in love with Bacino's a few years back and always go when we visit family in Chicago. They've really regressed. Toppings were mediocre. Crust dense. Hair on the salad. Hopefully it was just that day and not the new norm.

Pleasantly surprised by quality, portion size and true Italian flavor. It will be my go to place for yummy pizza and pasta.

I've been coming to this restaurant since I was a young child. My pop use to bring me and my brothers here. We haven't had a bad meal or service at this place since I can remember coming. Really great service and the spinach deep dish pizza is there signature entree. That's just my opinion. But all in all everything is worth your time and money, nice atmosphere, great for family and friends to get together and enjoy a great meal, awesome prices you can't beat it.
Awesome..as good as we remembered from our last visit ten years ago.

I wish I could comment on the food but was unable to order. My wife and I entered the restaurant about 10:25 pm giving us a whole 35 minutes before they closed. The boy at the counter asked if we were wanting to dine in and we said yes. He then proceeded to say, “Well we are actually going to close soon” and he wouldn’t seat us allowing us to stand there until  giving us the impression that he didn’t want our business. I totally understand it’s late and you want to go home, but in my retail days I never would have said that to a customer. That being said my wife and I left. I am very confused on why you would turn business away around 10:25 when your sign says your serve until 11:00pm?
meh. get what you pay for I guess

Excellent atmosphere, selection, and service.  We had the Bacino Special Double Crust pizza.  It is very likely the best pizza that I have ever had. Eduardo - our server - was very pleasant and attentive.  Bacino's has figured out what is important to their customers and they deliver it with enthusiasm.  Great job!!
I've eaten a lot of pizza in my life but this was some of the pizza the I've ever had. If you're in Chicago and you like pizza, I highly recommend checking this place out.
The pizza was really good and the portobello mushroom we had for an appetizer was amazing.

As a Chicago native..... This is the best pizza in town. Naples, Baccis, and Lou Malnatis has nothing on the Bacinos.
Great pizza and salad. Get the Arugula salad and stuffed spinach pie!
Best pizza in ALL of chicago! This is one of my absolute favorite places to eat, I’ll never stop coming back! Highly highly recommend.
Excellent stuffed pizza. Tip to people planning to order a stuffed pizza: it is best to order an appetizer to snack on while the stuffed pizza cooks as it takes a little while (but worth the wait).
Nasty overpriced pizza !!
Great food and service. The atmosphere was nice and chill. We will be back, for sure, next time we stop through.
Best deep dish period!

This is probably the most underrated pizza place that I have been to in the city. It has become my go-to for visits from out-of-towners. The deep dish is superb. The sauce is a little more acidic than most places, but the cheese balances it out perfectly. There is a decent selection of beer (craft and domestic). I have had different servers each time that I have visited and all have been very friendly and courteous. I have never had to wait to be seated, and the wait for food is shorter than Gino's/Giordano's/Lou Malnati's. You can actually hold a conversation unlike the other places too as it isn't loud and bustling.
Great Italian kitchen, love their menu
Lovely & warmful welcome. It was our first deep dish pizza and it was very good with à very large meal for very ecomic prices!

I was in Chicago on business 20 years ago and ate here. Ever since, when I think of Chicago, I think of this place. My family and I just came back to Chicago , so we came here. My children ordered spaghetti and meatballs. My son dies not usually like meat, but devoured the meatballs. The gravy was delicious. The event brought fresh bread which was good to soak up the sauce. My wife and I split a small, stuffed crust spinach and mushroom pizza. That was what I ordered all those years ago. The marinara was balanced. The crust was almost like a pie. It was cooked perfectly with a slight, crumbly crunch. The mozzarella was plentiful and mixed with spinach and mushrooms. Worth the wait. Probably the best pizza I have ever had.
Great pizza and wonderful atmosphere!
Delicious food. Warm atmospherd.

There's a reason why Bacino's is a fav among Chicago's top chefs. Their deep-dish pizza is Chicago's best. The crust is buttery, light and crispy. The sauce is chunky, succulent and generous in quantity. And the classic spinach/spinach and mushroom pie is *filled* with fresh greens. Salads and apps are tasty, too. And there's always a nice selection of craft beers on tap, with flights available. The dining room and bathrooms are a bit too "blast-from-the-past," but the booths are huge and comfy, and given the food, it's well worth overlooking the decor.
People were nice. Pizza was not. Do not get the pizza!
Pizza was la bamba! Loved it!
Great deep dish pizza
The pizza is very good, which is the most important thing. The garlic bread is also good. The service is good, and everyone is friendly. We had a reall good time both times we were there

We were here for my Sons 30th birthday celebration . The atmosphere is casual, the wait staff very courteous and the food is excellent! We had 2 appetizers , Bruschetta & deep fried Ravioli. I'm not a fan of either but found myself liking both. There was 8 of us so we decided on 3 pizzas, a deep dish sausage & pepperoni; a deep dish sausage & green pepper; and a thin crust sausage & mushroom. Just the right amount of ingredients to make them yummy! They have specialty drinks & craft beers, don't look for frozen drinks, they don't make them. We are from the South side and we have been here twice. We will more than likely go back again! They except reservations and also have a party room for really large groups downstairs. If you are looking  for a really good pizza, try Bacino's, you won't be disappointed!
Super yummy Chicago style deep dish pizza. They call it "stuffed" 😃
Pizza is Great and Pear salad w/gorgonzola cheese is worth going for.

Cute little place. The stuffed spinach pizza is awesome!! Way more flavorful than Giordano’s that just puts the spinach and no seasonings. Definitly coming back!
Great taste! Pizza wasn't ask warm as I wished for but was very good!
The small is more than enough to fill two people just for a heads up. The pizza is amazing! The cheese is what stands out the most. I recommend adding jalepeno and pepperoni to your order.

Good pizza, especially their deep dish. They're local to me and open relatively late, priced affordably, and I've rarely had to wait.
Excellent deep dish and good beer.
Amazing staff. ...warm reception and heart warming food!!😊
Very good pizza. I love that they have a personal 6" option. Small dining room and street parking only, so be warned. Right next to Oz Park.
The food here was incredible! A little pricy but very filling. It was a good deep dish. The sausage was better than lou malnati for me! Definitely a must visit
Great pizza!

Very tasty thick or thin stuffed pizza, but beware of how greasy and messy they can be! The cheese is very thick and the sauce is marinara - as opposed to Giordano's which have chunks of tomato. The establishment itself is a little cramped, but should be fine for groups of 4 or less.

I really enjoy the deep dish/stuffed pizza here. It's kind of a hidden gem in the neighborhood as I've never seen it crowded. Most people, or tourists anyway, tend to go to Chicago Pizza & Oven Grinder Co over on Clark St - while their pizza is good, it's not worth the 2-3 hour wait you'll encounter all the time there. The deep dish at Bacinos is classic Chicago, delicious and filled with ingredients - they don't fill half the pie with dough like they do over at Giordano's. In summary - skip the waits and overhyped pizza elsewhere and come here!
Good was great, atmosphere was very nice.

Fabulous pizza! Deep dish yet crust is nice and light! Try the spinach garlic bread!

Bacinos is historically one of the "gold standard" pizzas against which everything else is compared. They've been around over 30 years and they do stuffed pizza rather well.  You'll want to order the signature spinach stuffed pizza, (and give it 30-40 minutes to cook.) The wonderful blend of cheeses and spinach is truly delectable, and it flows into your plate.  The crust is hand-tossed with a pie crust delicacy. The cheese is voluminous and excellent, and the sauce is bright and alive.  (They make a thinner crust pizza that is equally tasty, but unexceptional.) The stuffed spinach pie is your target.

Well worth the wait! We were worried by the charter bus full of people that arrived shortly before us. It took 30 minutes to be seated (not too bad for Friday at 6:30), the front counter seemed disorganized, and there wasn't really anywhere to wait for our table but........ABSOLUTELY WORTH IT!!!!!! The appetizers were great but the deep dish was perfect! Our server was very apologetic about the delays but both he and the rest of the staff were very attentive. Great pizza place and ayran entire family loved it!
Always a delight!!!! From servers to food all is 100% satisfaction best pizza i've ever eaten!!!!!! I come all the way from Milwaukee,wi just to eat this incredible piece of heaven 😍😍😍
My favorite deep dish place in the city. Great prices, and awesome pizza. Beer selection isn't bad either.

Great prices, generous portions, wonderful service.

I do have to thank Miguel and the driver with working with me today in letting me get a pizza (as a gift to my physical therapist's office) at the edge of the delivery zone. Stuffed pizza from Bacino's is the best!  Amazing stuffed pizza.  When visiting Chicago and in this area, I always call ahead & have them par-bake two.  Then I take them home and finish cooking.  Always the best!!

We got the calamari appetizer and the stuffed pizza. The food was absolutely delicious and the service was great. Our waitress was attentive and very nice. We were seated immediately and our food came out quickly. Well worth the visit!
The pizza was absolutely delicious... And the wine too. Only pizza place over been to in Chicago, but the reviews did not let me down. Exceptional food and service

I enjoyed my experience here a lot. The stuffed pizza is similar to Giordano's in my opinion. I also tried the calamari which was pretty good. I think the beer prices are too high but the food prices are a good value so it evens out.

We stopped in to carb load before the Marathon and were not disappointed. The pasta portions were generous and the meatball sliders were really great. Unlike a lot of meatball sandwiches, at Bacino's they slice the meatballs, which makes things way more manageable and enjoyable. We would definitely go back.
The deep dish spinach pizza is my favorite, but they also have thin crust pizza for non-deep dish folks. The service can be a bit slow, but the pizza makes it worth it.
